                            <comment id="14468120" author="paulk" created="Fri, 6 Nov 2009 17:48:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes, it is a little tricky to deal with. Certainly making the change that you suggest alters the behavior so that your scenario works without breaking the current test suite. I haven&apos;t thought through further ramifications of the change though.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The workaround is to register your property missing handler for the subtype before you create any instances or register the property missing handler on an/each instance.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
